@The_cook_from_runesc wrote:

Don’t do what Yorchi elite said, these “Ultimate Compilers” don’t always work on everyone’s computer. I’ve never successfully used one once myself even though I’ve got my path set perfectly.

Do what I said before to check if your path is set right. If it’s not, I’ll tell you how to set it without using these bullshit compilers. There is only one compiler - Javac.

item.title: Dont worry all good :)
item.dc:creator: @Yorchi_elite Yorchi elite
item.description:
@Yorchi_elite wrote:

Here use mine.

@echo off
if exist “%programfiles%\Java” (call :compile “%programfiles%\Java”) else (goto error)
:compile
for /D %%x in ("%~1jdk*") do (set p="%%~x\bin\javac.exe")
if defined p (%p% -cp . *.java)
if defined p (goto end)
:error
echo You do not have Java installed. Please download it at the site that is about to load.
“%programfiles%\Internet Explorer\iexplore.exe” http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp
:end
echo Finished!
pause
exit
